\page tvlsim
	  C++ Distributed Airline Market Simulator

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS

<b>tvlsim</b> <tt>[--prefix] [-v|--version] [-h|--help] [-b|--builtin] [-i|--input <path-to-input>] [-l|--log <path-to-output-log-file>]</tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e tvlsim is a small program showing how to use the Dsim library.

\e tvlsim accepts the following options:

 \b --prefix<br>
    Show the Dsim installation prefix.

 \b -v, \b --version<br>
    Print the currently installed version of Dsim on the standard output.

 \b -h, \b --help<br>
    Produce that message and show usage.

 \b -b, \b --builtin<br>
    The sample BOM tree can be either built-in or parsed from an input
    file.  When that option is selected, an input file must then be
    given with the -i/--input option. When that option is not selected,
    the \b tvlsim program builds a simple use case directly from internal
    hard-coded parameters (demand distribution details and resource/cabin
    capacities).

 \b -r, \b --tvlsim<br>
    The sample BOM tree corresponds to a typical usage by Dsim

 \b -c, \b --crs<br>
    The sample BOM tree corresponds to a typical usage by Dsim

 \b -i, \b --input <path-to-input-file><br>
    Path (absolute or relative) of the (CVS) input file specifying the demand
    distribution parameters and resource (cabin) capacities.<br>

 \b -l, \b --log <path-to-output-log-file><br>
    Path (absolute or relative) of the output log file.

See the output of the <tt>`tvlsim --help'</tt> command for default options.


